claims:
Claims CLAIMS 1. A method of detecting a diabetic complication in a subject comprising: (i) quantifying a N 2 -(1-carboxyethyl)-guanosine (CEG) level in a biological sample from the subject comprising: (a) performing a liquid chromatography electrospray ionizing tandem mass spectrometry (LC-ESI-MS/MS) assay on the biological sample using a stable isotope dilution comprising using an internal 15 N 5 -(1-carboxyethyl)-guanosine ( 15 N 5 -CEG) standard comprising stereochemically pure 15 N5-CEG (R) and stereochemically pure 15 N5-CEG (S); and (b) measuring the CEG level in the biological sample; and (ii) determining the subject has the diabetic complication when the CEG level in the biological sample is elevated as compared to a normal physiological CEG level. 2. The method of claim 1, further comprising administering a treatment for the diabetic complication to the subject determined to have the diabetic complication. 3. The method of claim 2, further comprising after administering the treatment for the diabetic complication, determining whether the treatment is therapeutically effective by repeating the method steps of claim 1. 4. The method of any one of claims 1-3, wherein the diabetic complication is caused by a metabolic disorder or metabolic disease. 5. The method of any one of claims 1-4, wherein the biological sample is a urine sample, blood sample, serum sample, or a tissue sample. 6. The method of any one of claims 1-5, wherein quantifying the level of CEG comprises quantifying the level of CEG (S) and CEG (R). 7. The method of any one of claims 1-6, wherein the internal 15 N5-CEG standard comprises oligonucleotides containing stereochemically pure 15 N5-CEG (R) and 

 oligonucleotides containing stereochemically pure 15 N5-CEG (S). 8. The method of any one of claims 1-7, wherein the assay quantifies a level of CEG of less than 0.1 nanogram/milliliter. 9. The method of any one of claims 1-8, wherein the diabetic complication is selected from the group consisting of a microvascular or macrovascular complication; hyperosmolar hyperglycemic nonketotic syndrome (HHNS), hyperlipidemia, coronary artery disease (CAD), ketoacidosis, foot and skin ulceration and damage, hearing impairment, Alzheimerâs disease, and cancer. 10. The method of claim 9, wherein the microvascular or macrovascular complication is selected from the group consisting of hypertension, stroke, cardiovascular diseases, neuropathy, nephropathy, and retinopathy. 11. A method of synthesizing an internal standard comprising a stereochemically pure 15 N 5 -(1-carboxyethyl)-guanosine ( 15 N 5 -CEG) (R) and stereochemically pure 15 N 5 -CEG (S), the method comprising: (i) generating a mixture comprising mixing DL-glyceraldehyde with 15 N5-labeled guanosine monophosphate ( 15 N 5 -GMP) and sodium phosphate in water; (ii) heating the mixture; and (iii) purifying stereochemically pure 15 N5-CEG (R) and stereochemically pure 15 N5- CEG (S) from the mixture using high-performance liquid chromatography (HPLC). 12. The method of claim 11, wherein the 15 N 5 -CEG (R) and 15 N 5 -CEG (S) are further dephosphorylated. 13. A method of synthesizing an internal standard comprising oligonucleotides comprising stereochemically pure 15 N 5 -(1-carboxyethyl)-guanosine ( 15 N 5 -CEG) (R) and oligonucleotides comprising stereochemically pure 15 N5-CEG (S), the method comprising: (i) generating RNA oligonucleotides containing 2-fluoro-inosine (2-FI); 

 (ii) mixing the 2-FI RNA oligonucleotides with D- or L-alanine in potassium carbonate to form a mixture; (iii) heating the mixture in concentrated ammonia; and (iv) purifying oligonucleotides comprising stereochemically pure 15 N5-CEG (R) and oligonucleotides comprising stereochemically pure 15 N5-CEG (S) from the mixture using ion-pairing chromatography.
